sections.text:
Processing facilities should, to the extent possible, be located close to the source of raw materials so as to minimize changes that might lead to quality or safety concerns for raw materials of quick frozen foods prior to freezing.

The temperature measuring device used to measure product temperature should be of better accuracy than that used for air temperature monitoring . The following specifications are recommended for the system, i.e. sensor and read-out:
 the system should have an accuracy of 6 0.56C within the measuring range -206C to +306C;
 the response time should achieve 90% of the difference between initial and final readings within three minutes;
 the display resolution of the read-out should be 0.16C;
 the measuring accuracy should not change by more than 0.3 6C during operation in the ambient range -206C to +306C;
 the system should be calibrated or otherwise verified prior to use and at specified intervals against measurement standards traceable to international or national measurement standards;
 the accuracy of the system should be checked at regular intervals;
 the system should be robust and the device and equipment should be shock-proof; and
 the electrical components of the system should be protected against undesirable effects due to condensation of moisture.

